<TITLE>Scope of Comments: MN Utility Deregulation</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<CENTER><H3>STATE OF MINNESOTA<P>
BEFORE THE PUBLIC UTILITIES COMMISSION</H3>
<BR>
In the Matter of an Investigation into Docket E-999/CI-95-135<BR>
Structural and Regulatory Issues <BR>
in the Electric Utility Industry<BR>
</CENTER><P>
<HR>

<CENTER><B>COMMENTS OF MINNESOTANS FOR AN ENERGY EFFICIENT ECONOMY<P>
July 7, 1995</B><P></CENTER>

<H4>C.  SCOPE OF COMMENTS</H4>
ME3 has limited its Comments to issues of particular concern. These include Comments on Sections A(1)(2)(3); B(2)(a)(b)(c)(d); B(3)(a)(b)(c); B(4)(a)(b); B(5)(a)(c)(d); C(1)(a); C(2)(a)(b)(c) as specified in Attachment "A" of the Commission's May 8, 1995 Order.<P>

