<HEAD>
<TITLE>Full and Fair Consideration of the Issues:  MN Utility Deregulation Reply</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<CENTER><H3>STATE OF MINNESOTA<P>
BEFORE THE PUBLIC UTILITIES COMMISSION</H3>
<BR>
In the Matter of an Investigation into <BR>
Structural and Regulatory Issues <BR>
in the Electric Utility Industry<BR>
Docket E-999/CI-95-135
</CENTER><P>
<HR>

<CENTER><B>REPLY COMMENTS OF MINNESOTANS FOR AN ENERGY EFFICIENT ECONOMY<BR>
and<BR>
IZAAK WALTON LEAGUE OF AMERICA (MIDWEST OFFICE)<P>
September 11, 1995</B><P></CENTER>
<P>

<H3>7.  A Full and Fair Consideration of the Issues:  Getting the Process Right.</H3>
<P>
The ME3 Coalition and the IWLA again renew their request that the Commission request the Environmental Quality Board to conduct a full environmental impact statement (EIS) on the very important environmental and resource conservation questions which are so obviously raised by the radical restructuring proposals of many parties commenting in this docket. Only a systematic review of the environmental impacts of the policy decisions to be made can fully inform the decision-makers. It is our reading of the EIS statute that a full EIS would be required for any serious evaluation of the environmental issues raised by the radical proposals advanced in this docket. An environmental impact statement, for example, has recently be completed in Wisconsin to evaluate the impacts of potential utility restructuring on Wisconsin's environment.<P>
Additionally, a contested-case hearing would be a useful forum to resolve the factual issues in dispute.<P>
Lastly, if any additional stakeholder forums are established for substantive policy discussions on these important matters, we would respectfully request an adequate representation of multiple public interest perspectives, as well as utilities other than IOUs. In the prior effort in this regard , the Chairman's Rountable which met intermittently from 1992-1994, only state agencies, investor-owned utilities and a sole representative of diverse public interest views were represented.<P>

</BODY>
</HTML>

</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT15-B08-23</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA007-000067-B012-232</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://www.me3.org:80/projects/dereg/restruct1.html 198.174.235.57 19970222005132 text/html 17117
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
