<A NAME="v"><H2>V. MISCELLANEOUS INFORMATION</H2>
<H3>Good Reason for Energy Independence!</H3>
Have you noticed that a gallon of gasoline is about 25% more expensive than it was 6-12 months ago? The prices of fuel, natural gas, propane and fuel oil have all been on the rise.  For Minnesota consumers it means that we are spending up to 25 percent more for imported fuels.  In the case of gasoline, Minnesotans will send about $200 million out of the state.
 When will the increases in energy prices be sufficient to generate the interest of policymakers and regulators in nurturing our homegrown energy industries?<P>

