<a name="fn18">[18]</a> Water contains 12 percent hydrogen versus 6 percent for biomass.
But conversion efficiencies of biomass to hydrogen are higher.  Conversion
efficiencies of 70 percent have been achieved by biomass gasification system.
Conversion efficiencies to methanol using the same system would be 62 percent.
A similar scaled water electrolysis hydrogen production system is 55 percent
efficient.<p>
  <p>
<a name="fn19">[19]</a> M.A. DeLuchi, E.D. Larson, R.H. Williams, <i>Biomass Methanol and
