<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Enercheck Systems Inc. - Off Peak Emergency Circuit</TITLE></HEAD><BODY  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Enercheck Systems Inc</H1> <BR><CENTER><FONT SIZE=4>and</FONT></CENTER><BR> <H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Energy Reclamation Corporation</H1><P><HR><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Off Peak Emergency Circuit (OPEC) </H2><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>The OPEC System: Technology for Energy Self-Reliance</H3>OPEC is an advanced electrical storage/inversion system that gives homeowners and small businesses the ability to store up to 72 hours of emergency power.<P>The OPEC system provides energy insurance and peace of mind against increasingly reoccurring power failures.<P>This state-of-the-art system also allows you the opportunity to purchase power at off-peak rates, slashing your utility bills by 50% or more per month.  In essence, the OPEC system can literally pay for itself by capturing electricity at lower costs, storing it, and providing it for your use during on-peak, high-cost hours.<P><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>How OPEC Works</H3>The heart of the OPEC system is a control relay station that functions in conjunction with your current circuit breaker panel.When your next power failure occurs the control relay station will automatically disconnect from your utility company's grid system and switch to the OPEC's energy reserve.  The system is re-energized after utility power is restored.<P><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>OPEC System Economics</H3>The cost of your system will vary from $1,595 to $3,685 depending on the load (electrical devices) that you wish to control.<P>The system can be expanded as your needs change, and each OPEC system includes a full two year parts and labor guarantee.<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Why OPEC is Necessary</H3>Due to population growth, an ever-increasing demand for electricity and reliability problems associated with existing delivery systems, power failures are becoming more and more disruptive.<P>Power failures are a serious concern in the winter months, but they can also cause major problems during the rest of the year.  For example, if the power fails in the spring during the flooding season, or during a major rain storm, and the sump pump cannot function to get the water out of th basement, most insurance companies will not cover the damages.A major utility is planning to utilize the OPEC System to protect senior citizens from the lethal effects of the loss of grid power during the extreme heat of summer.  OPEC can provide cooling fans which could prevent heat exhaustion. <P><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>What's the Answer</H3>Until recent technological advances, the answer for emergency back-up electricity has been cumbersome generators powered by fuel.  Generators are expensive to operate, only work if you are there to hook it up and start it, and typically run for only a few hours.  Now there's an alternative.<P>At prices starting under $1600, Enercheck Systems or Energy Reclamation Corporation can now equip your home, small business, or barn with an electrical storage system called an Off Peak Emergency Circuit (OPEC).  Because an OPEC stores up to 72 hours of power, you'll never again be left in the dark.<P><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Here's How the OPEC Works</H3>The heart of the OPEC component system is a control relay station that functions in conjunction with your circuit breaker panel.  When your next power failure occurs, the control relay station will automatically disconnect from your utility company's grid system (power lines) and tap into an energy reserve stored at your location.  This reserve will power what you consider to be your daily essential.  For some, heat and light will suffice.  For others, more electricity will be required.  No matter what the season, or what your needs are, the OPEC system will provide you with the emergency power you demand - while other are scrambling for generators or heading for the emergency shelters.<P><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>An OPEC System Can Pay for Itself</H3>By combining emerging technologies, this state-of-the-art system can be programmed to purchase power from your utility company at off peak rates, slashing your electrical bills by 50% or more per month.  In essence, an OPEC can literally pay for itself by capturing electricity at lower costs, storing it, and providing it for your use during high-demand hours.<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>An OPEC is Your Link to Energy Self-Sufficiency</H3>Because of the OPEC's ability to interface with existing utility suppliers and capture power at off-peak rates, you can now take a bite out of your ever-increasing electrical costs.  In addition, the OPEC has been thoughtfully designed to convert and store power from solar, wind, and other electrical generating systems.  <P>Should you ever desire to become self-sufficient and sustainable, and say goodbye to your current provider we have the expertise and competitively priced products to get you there.  Considering the waste and pollution generated by nuclear and coal power plants, steps toward self-sufficiency will be a great way for you to save money and honor the Earth.<P>Contact us for further information at the following address:<P><CENTER><B>Enercheck Systems Inc</B> <BR>191 West 5th Street <BR>Cottonwood, MN  56229 <BR>(507) 423-5547<BR>E-mail:  <!-- MailTo Tag --><A HREF="MAILTO:djuhl@polaristel.net">Dan Juhl</A>,  (djuhl@polaristel.net)</CENTER><P><CENTER><B>Energy Reclamation Corporation</B> <BR>2801 18th Avenue South <BR>Minneapolis, MN  55407<BR>(612) 722-4951 </CENTER><HR>Return to the <A HREF="http://www.me3.org/">Sustainable Minnesota Home Page</A></BODY></HTML>
