<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Minnesota Tax Shift Case Study Form</H2>
   <H3>Background:</H3>
 The <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.ilsr.org/">Institute for Local Self-Reliance (ILSR)</A>  and <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.me3.org/">Minnesotans for an Energy-Efficient Economy (ME3)</A> are conducting research on the effects of a proposed tax shift in Minnesota.  The  shift would raise taxes on fuels by approximately $1.5 billion and reduce taxes by an equivalent amount on property and/or payroll taxes.  Based on a preliminary analysis, shifting taxes in this way could reduce pollution and expand employment and economic growth.<P>


 
 ILSR and ME3 are conducting surveys of actual businesses and residents in Minnesota to assess the impact of the $1.5 billion tax shift.  We appreciate your participation in making our research successful.<P>


 
 <B>Only Minnesota site data is requested.</B><P>


 
 <B>Confidentiality:</B> Names and data of individual companies/residents will not be released. For example, if Jane's Barber Shop supplies information the data will be identified under a general business classification ("barber shop" or "small business").<P>

<HR>
 
 
