<HTML VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD><TITLE>Indian Arts
and Crafts Association - Promoting, Preserving and Protecting Native American
Creations</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BACKGROUND="./iaca_bg2.gif" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#00ff00">
<CENTER><H1>Indian Arts and Crafts Association</H1> 
<IMG SRC="./iacalogo.gif" ALT="IACA Logo"> <IMG SRC="../images/cp_blk.gif"> 
<H3> Promoting, Preserving and Protecting<BR> NATIVE AMERICAN CREATIONS</H3></CENTER>
<P></P> 
<P> The Indian Arts and Crafts Association (IACA) is a not-for-profit
organization established  in 1974 to support the effective protection and
ethical promotion of authentic Native American  art and material culture. IACA
has more than 700 members throughout the United States and five  foreign
countries. Members include Native American artists, wholesale and retail
dealers, museums, collectors and others who support the goals of the
organization.</P> 
<P></P> 
<UL>
<LI><B><A HREF="./products.htm">Consumer Education</A></B> - Through its
publications, demonstrations and seminars, IACA promotes understanding of
authentic handmade Indian arts and crafts and helps consumers know what to look
for when buying Indian products.</LI> 
<LI><B><A HREF="./member.htm">Advocacy</A></B> - IACA acts as an advocate for
the Indian arts and crafts industry in support of state and federal laws
protecting artists, dealers and consumers against fakes and imported
reproductions. Helps set standards for the industry on quality and authenticity.</LI>
<LI><B><A HREF="./artists.htm">Promotes Indian Artists</A></B> - IACA offers
Indian artists and craftspeople business education and marketing assistance.
Promotes outstanding Indian artist as IACA &quot;Artist of the Year.&quot;
Provides profiles on Indian artists to member galleries and dealers. 

</LI> 
<LI><B><A HREF="./markets.htm">Indian Art Wholesale Markets</A></B> - IACA
conducts the only wholesale trade shows exclusively devoted to authentic
handmade Indian arts and crafts.</LI> 
<LI>Index of <I><A HREF="./art.htm"><B>IACA Artist Craftsperson Members</B></A></I>
and an index of <I><A HREF="./wholedat.htm"> <B>Wholesale and Retail Indian
Arts and Crafts Dealers</B></A></I>.
</LI> 
</UL>
<P></P> 
<P><B><I>For membership, publications or market information, contact:</I></B></P>
<CENTER><P> INDIAN ARTS AND CRAFTS ASSOCIATION<BR>  122 La Veta NE, Suite B
Albuquerque, NM 87108<BR>  Phone: (505)265-9149<BR>  Fax: (505)265-8251<BR>
email: <A HREF="mailto:iaca@ix.netcom.com">iaca@ix.netcom.com</A></P></CENTER>
