<HEAD>
<TITLE>Welcome to ATIIN, Inc. - Providing Internet and World Wide Technologies</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#B07743" LINK="#FFF9B0" VLINK="#FFF9B0"><CENTER><IMG
ALIGN="TOP" SRC="../images/whowe.jpg"></CENTER><CENTER><BR><H2>&quot;Where Tradition Meets Technology&quot;</H2></CENTER>
<P><BR></P><P><B>'atiin</B> - a Navajo word for roadway or pathway - symbolizes the
Information Superhighway and the desire to integrate <A HREF="./creation.htm">culture
and technolgy.</A> </P><P>The founders of ATIIN,  are all Native American engineers and system
administrators with backgrounds and expertise in the telecommunication and R&amp;D
environments.  The common thread in ATIIN's wide range of initiatives is the
desire to foster economic development through access to and knowledge of
technology.</P>  
<P>
ATIIN's technological skills will be utilized to create an &quot;Economic
Development Model&quot;, that can be implemented across cultures by providing
state-of-the-art, technological methods of: 
</P><P><IMG ALIGN="TOP" SRC="../images/button.jpg" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20"> Providing world wide presence on the Internet by installing a central Web
server to provide <A HREF="./website.htm">Web Services.</A><BR> 
<IMG ALIGN="TOP" SRC="../images/button.jpg" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20"> Creating telecommunication
infrastucture by  providing <A HREF="./lanwan.htm">consulting services</A> to
design and implement  infrastructure utilizing Web technology.<BR> 
<IMG ALIGN="TOP" SRC="../images/button.jpg" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20"> Training our clients to maintain
and utilize existing technologies such as training
sessions to utilize Web technology. 
</P>
<P>ATIIN Inc. has the distinction of being one of the first successful
companies of the Technology Transfer efforts of <A HREF="http://www.sandia.gov">
Sandia National Laboratories</A>. The alliances with this research leader and
other  companies makes ATIIN the primary resource for Web technology expertise
for our clients. Our board of directors consist of the founders and outside
management advisors for support of our management decisions and creatiity.
</P> 
<P><I><B>Board of Directors</B></I>
</P>
<UL><LI>Laurence E. Brown - President</LI>
<LI>Robert A. Mora - Secretary Treasurer</LI>
<LI>Dwight Guerneau - Director (President Metis Incorporated)</LI>
<LI>Kenneth Hunt - Director (CEO/President Arrowhead Industries)</LI>

</UL>
<P><I><B>Alliances</B></I>
</P>
<UL><LI><A HREF="http://www.atiin.com/grayngray/">Gray &amp; Gray Advertising</A></LI>
<LI>Alliance for Technological Entrepeneurs (Sandia National Laboratory)
</LI><LI><A HREF="http://www.sandia.gov/ttrans/ttrans.html">Sandia National 
Laboratories Technology Transfer</A> - Albuquerque, NM
</LI>
