<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Spider Woman Strikes Again!</TITLE></HEAD><BODY
BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#B07743" LINK="#FFF9B0" VLINK="#FFF9B0"><CENTER><IMG
SRC="../images/spider.jpg" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="20"><TR><TD COLSTART="1"><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" SRC="../images/spdrck1.jpg" ALT="Spider Rock - Canyon de Chelly" BORDER="2"></TD><TD
COLSTART="2"><H2>Integrating Culture and Technology:</H2>

<FONT SIZE="+4">S</FONT><FONT SIZE="+3">pider</FONT> <FONT SIZE="+4">W</FONT><FONT
SIZE="+3">oman:</FONT>



<UL>

<LI>Originator of spinning and weaving</LI>

<LI>Trickery</LI>

<LI>Gives gifts of the feathers</LI>

<LI>Uses a web as a savior</LI>

<LI>Web of life</LI>

</UL>

<P></P>

<P><FONT SIZE="+4">N</FONT>avajo Culture depicts Spider Woman as the weaver of life and originator of spinning.  Her abilities are  emulated in the products of the textile industry and is shown in the beauty and creativity of the Navajo rug.  As she continues through life she emerges once again by striking with another gift; the weaving of the World Wide Web.</P>


</TD></TR></TABLE>

