<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HTML VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD><TITLE>Arrow Fax Inc., - First Nations Tribal Directory</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="./tribal.gif"></CENTER>

<P>Welcome to the second edition of the FIRST NATIONS TRIBAL DIRECTORY. North America's comprehensive Indian Country telephone book.</P>

<P>The First Nations/Tribal communities are in the forefront in utilizing modern communications technology to join Native Americans. Essentially creating one big network from coast to coast to coast to coast.</P>

<P>Arrowfax is proud to be part of this; by listing all the Tribes, First Nations, Inuit, and Metis, their governments, departments, their organizations, businesses, institutions, and their programs in the Arrowfax directory. Also listed are Urban Native Americans and their enterprises and organizations.</P>

<P>Publication Dates: Arrowfax intends to publish an updated directory twice a year. The next publication date is January 1996.</P>

<P>PRE-PUBLICATION SALE: The normal <B>after publication price</B> for our directory is $40.00; however, if you place a pre-publication order during November &amp; December of 1995, you will receive a 20% discount. To receive this discount, fill out the order form below, and send a check or money order to:</P>

