<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//SQ//DTD HTML 2.0 HoTMetaL + extensions//EN">
<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Arrow Fax Inc. - Corporate Profile</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><IMG SRC="./corporat.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER><P>ARROWFAX is a Native American company, founded in the fall of 1988 in order to enlarge and promote communication among Native Americans. ARROWFAX has already played its role in renewing ancestral trading links - it is networking at its best.</P><P>ARROWFAX published it's first Native American directory (address, phone, and fax number) in the spring of 1989. The 90's were launched with the publication of the ARROWFAX NATIONAL DIRECTORY, country wide in Canada. To date, twelve ARROWFAX directories have been produced, making even the most remote communities part of the network - our goal is to make Native America into one big neighborhood.</P><P>Three years ago, ARROWFAX entered the U.S. market with the first edition of the North American Tribal Gaming Directory. After two such publications, ARROWFAX decided to incorporate the gaming Directory into the latest and most comprehensive First Nations Tribal Directory.</P><P>ARROWFAX now looks forward to expanding to include Mexico and in the near future, Central and South America.</P><P>Currently, however, ARROWFAX is moving from the printed word to electronic media with the production of an ARROWFAX CD-ROM - and now, &quot;welcome to the Internet!&quot;</P><P>ARROWFAX has been financed entirely through the sale of directories, sale of advertising, and database sales. It operates a continent-wide network and database - the most comprehensive and up-to-date Native American database, enabling immediate access by name, address, phone/fax and E-mail to Tribes, First Nations/Indian, Inuit, and Metis - Native American governments, organizations, associations, institutions, and businesses.</P><P>Our database is constantly updated - do not hesitate to contact us with additions or corrections. We value your help in keeping the ARROWFAX Database current and accurate.</P><CENTER><ADDRESS><B>Editorial Office:<BR>P.O. Box 66009, Unicity Postal Outlet<BR>Winnipeg, MB, R3K 2E7<BR>Tel: (204) 864-2488<BR>Fax: (204) 864-2598</B></ADDRESS><P><BR>
<BR>
