<HTML><HEAD>    
<TITLE>CORPORATE</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="PHOTOS/wood.gif" TEXT="#103437" ALINK="#ff232d"><IMG
ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="PHOTOS/trade1.gif"><IMG
ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="PHOTOS/spacer.gif" WIDTH="12" HEIGHT="48"><IMG
ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="PHOTOS/lhsp1.gif"><IMG
SRC="PHOTOS/spacer.gif" WIDTH="12" HEIGHT="48" ALIGN="bottom">
<P><BR>Angela DeMontigny<BR>Designer/President <BR>of SPIRIT WARE <BR><BR><BR><B>THE
SPIRIT WARE COLLECTION<BR><BR><STRONG>F</STRONG></B>or thousands of years
Native Americans have been creating beautiful artwork, <BR>inspired from a
spiritual love and reverence for nature. I have tried to capture the <BR>essence
of my own Native heritage by providing the link between the historical
historical past  <BR>and the present through the design of the clothing and
accessories presented presented in our <BR>1996 Collection.<BR><BR>Traditional
techniques such as beadwork and embroidery have been used to<BR>decorate <B><I>thoroughly
modern garments</I></B><I> </I>which are as practical as they are <BR>beautiful.
In keeping with our deep respect for Mother Earth, all of the fabrics we have<BR>chosen
are 100% natural - we have even used a new, recycled cotton fabric called <BR><B>&quot;Ecofibre&quot;</B>.
Attention to details such as using natural wood buttons (leftovers from <BR>logged
areas in British Columbia) and screen printing with environmentally safe, <BR>water-based
inks are all part of this inherent philosophy.<BR><BR>It is also important to
emphasize that <B>Spirit Ware</B> is a fully Native-owned company, <BR>based
on the Six Nations Reserve of the Grand River Territory in Ontario, Canada and
<BR>that all of the designs and symbols used in this collection are <B>&quot;authentic&quot;</B>.Every
time <BR>a <B>Spirit Ware</B> item is purchased, the proceeds go back to
Native peoples and local <BR>communities. It is only through entrepreneurial
projects such as this that self sufficiency <BR>and the protection of spiritual
and environmental integrity within Native communities will <BR>be achieved.
<B>Spirit Ware </B>is committed to this cause, especially the continued growth
of <BR>an established First Nations textile and clothing industry.<BR><BR>Much
thought and care has gone into the creation of this collection. Be inspired by
its Spirit.<BR>Nya:weh (Thank you) <BR><IMG
ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="PHOTOS/name.gif" WIDTH="270" HEIGHT="105"><BR>Angela
DeMontigny, <BR>Designer/President of Spirit Ware <BR>SIX NATIONS OF THE GRAND
</P>
