<HTML><HEAD>    
<TITLE>SW Accessories</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="PHOTOS/wood.gif" TEXT="#5a0e03"><H1></H1>
<H1></H1>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="PHOTOS/SWLogo.gif" WIDTH="472" HEIGHT="93" ALIGN="bottom"></CENTER>
<HR>
<P>Accessories</P>
<P></P>
<CENTER>Back to <A HREF="home.html">SpiritWare home page </A></CENTER>
<H4><I>Powerful, mystical symbols are silk screened and handpainted onto
DeMontigny's home-related items, as well as her personal accessories: jewelry
rolls, makeup brush holders, and compact or overnight-sized cosmetic bags.<BR>Buckskin
belt bags and eyeglass cases also carry the Spirit Ware deer logo, indicating
the designer's respect for the animal that has assisted in the survival of North
America's First Peoples.<BR>One of the line's unique items, a small drawstring
sac called a spirit pouch, also has a spot in Native heritage. Traditionally,
these pouches carried medicines, herbs and prized objects, and were worn around
the neck to protect individuals from negative forces. Today, they may simply
provide safe keeping for small personal belongings.</I></H4>
<P></P>
<CENTER></CENTER>
