COLSTART="1"></TD><TD COLSTART="2"><IMG
ALIGN="RIGHT" SRC="./images/construct.jpg"><A HREF="mailto:lcmfanch@alaska.net">LCMF</A> is a 100% Alaska Native-owned, full service architectural design, engineering, surveying, project management, and arctic research firm offering a broad range of services throughout Alaska.  LCMF provides design and construction management services for all types of buildings and facilities.  LCMF's survey group provides both land and hydrographic surveys.  As a wholly-owned subsidiary of Ukpeagvik I&ntilde;upiat Corporation (UIC), the village corporation of Barrow, LCMF:<UL><LI>Currently employs 41 full-time personnel (36 in Anchorage, 5 in Barrow)</LI><LI>Has completed over 1,300 projects in the last 14 years (without claims leading to litigation)</LI><LI>Has continually staffed offices in Anchorage since 1982 and Barrow since 1986.</LI></UL><BR><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" SRC="./images/diversify.gif"><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR><IMG
ALIGN="RIGHT" SRC="./images/catepillar.jpg">Management of LCMF is through a board of directors who are all shareholders of UIC and members of Barrow native community.  LCMF's current professional staff has extensive collective experience throughout the state of Alaska.  The staff is supported by state-of-the-art, field-to-finish computer hardware and software.  While a staff of support personnel is essential to successful projects services, we feel it is also essential that the company managers work with, and alongside, the staff to accomplish our client's goals.  The philosophy of our organization requires professional supervision at all phases of project development, particularly through bidding, construction and project close-out.</TD></TR></TABLE><CENTER><BR><B>Services Available<BR><BR></B></CENTER><TABLE
