<HR>
<P><A HREF="sulliv2.jpg"><IMG ALIGN="LEFT" SRC="sulliv1.jpg" ALT="sea poster"></A>
</P>
<P><B><I><A NAME="dsullivan">THE </A>SOLDIER'S LETTER </I></B>
</P>
<P>Original water color 24&quot; x 30&quot;, <BR><B><I>Dorothy Sullivan</I></B>,
Cherokee  S/N edition 300  15&quot; x 20&quot;  $60.00 
</P>
<P>A soldier wrote his wife of the suffering of the Cherokee on their Trail of
Tears and revealed his anguish as he picked up a baby from the arms of a dying
mother in the snow.  Many Americans protested the Indian Removal policy and
extended compassion and kindness to the displaced tribes.   </P>
<P>Book:  Cherokee Heritage Collection - 22 paintings; 7 years of research by
Dorothy  $24.00  
</P>
<P>Catalog $5.00   </P>
<P>MEMORY CIRCLE STUDIO, P.O. Box 732 Norman, Oklahoma 73070 (405)360-0751
</P>
