<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HTML VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD><TITLE>Technology Ventures Corporation - Mission and Achievements</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>
<BODY Background="./blue_bg.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFE">
<H1>MISSION</H1>
<P><B><I>Technology Ventures Corporation is a bridge between the public and private sectors for the commercialization
of technologies developed at the Department of Energy's national laboratories and national research universities.</B></I></P>

<IMG ALIGN="LEFT" src="./shake.gif"><B><P><I>A nonprofit organization established in 1993 by Martin 
Marietta, now Lockheed Martin, Technology Ventures identifies technologies with commercial potential,
coordinates the development of business and management capabilities and seeks sources of risk capital
for the business.</I></P></B>

<H1>ACHIEVEMENTS</H1>

<P></P>

<IMG ALIGN="left" src="./state.jpg"><menu><P>Technology Ventures greatest challenges&#151;finding technologies that can be commercialized and finding the funding necessary to bring them to commercial maturity&#151;have also emerged as its greatest successes. Recognized as a contributor to economic development on both regional and national levels, Technology Ventures after only two years in operation is seen as a source of viable new technologies by investors and as a path to funding by technologists. For Technology Ventures clients funding primarily comes from outside equity investors.</P>
<P><center><IMG  src="./graph.jpg"></P>
<P><B>Cumulative Value of Investments to TVC Clients</P></center></menu>

<P></P><center><img src="../images/barpurpl.gif"></center><P></P>
