<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HTML VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD><TITLE>Technology Ventures Corporation - Message from the President</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>
<body bgcolor="FFFFf0">
<H2>FROM THE PRESIDENT</H2>

<P>Our first two years have been a heady mix of challenge and success, of living up to our mission and at times, exceeding it.</P>

<P>Technology Ventures has succeeded in creating a viable channel for the commercialization of government-generated technologies. In so doing, we are increasing the value of those technologies. They are making a dual contribution. In government, they support our nations defense. In the private sector, they are creating jobs and enhancing the nation's industrial competitiveness.</P>

<IMG align="left" src="./sherman.jpg"><menu><P>Although Technology Ventures has accomplished much, we recognize that the future holds fresh challenges. As government-sponsored research facilities continue to pursue a Congressional mandate to move technology to the private sector, the need for our services will grow. And, as industry demands more and better technology, the importance of technology commercialization will grow even more, as will the need for the services we provide.</P>

<P>Therefore, we will maintain and continue to expand our risk-capital resources. We will continue to nurture the best technologies, and we will continue to work for economic development. We believe that we can expand our regional success into a national model for effective and efficient technology commercialization.</P>

<P></P>

<B><P>Sherman McCorkle</P>

<P>President</P></b></menu>

<P></P><center><img src="../images/barpurpl.gif"></center><P></P>

