<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//SQ//DTD HTML 2.0 HoTMetaL + extensions//EN">
<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Native Peoples Magazine - Passing the Torch (pt. 1)</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000"><TABLE CELLPADDING="10"><TR><TD
VALIGN="MIDDLE" COLSTART="1"><IMG SRC="./torch.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></TD><TD
ALIGN="CENTER" COLSTART="2"><IMG SRC="blanton.jpg" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><P><I>Bushyhead
and Blanton make an unbeatable team in dedication to the preservation project.</I></P><P
ALIGN="LEFT">Preservation, identity, and conversions are the key words necessary for
understanding the  article &quot;Passing the Torch&quot;. This article documents
Robert Bushyhead's attempt to save the Kituhwa dialect of the Cherokee language.
Bushyhead has incorporated the help of his daughter, linguists, and tribal
elders in his endeavor to systemize the language into various types of lessons
which are taught in classes from the elementary to the college level.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT">Many believe that the identity of a culture is inherent in the language. So
when a language becomes extinct, so does the identity of the people. This
identity includes the world view of a people. Bushyhead finds evidence of the
Cherokee world view in the syntax of the language.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT">Kituhwa dialect os one of four dialects of the Cherokee People. One of these
four dialects has already become extinct as a result of assimilation. First came
the mass forced migration of thousands of Cherokee people to Oklahoma in 1838.
Later, school officials began punishing children who spoke any language other
than English. Today, only the ;elders. like Bushyhead, are able to fluently
speak their native tongue.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT">Since the language is already written down, the push is to teach the young
children the spoken language. It is important to use the language in
conversation in order to understand all the nuances communicated in this
inflectional language. Video cameras record traditional practices such as
cooking, craft making, and story telling in English as well as the Kituhwa
dialect. Computers systematize the language with a dictionary and grammar text.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT">The eighty one year old Bushyhead passes the torch of language and culture
on to his daughter as well as the youth of the Cherokee Nation.</P></TD><TD
VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="RIGHT" COLSTART="3"><BR><BR><BR><BR><IMG
ALIGN="TOP" SRC="./saves.gif"></TD></TR>
</TABLE><CENTER><TABLE><TR><TD COLSTART="1"><A HREF="./toc.htm"><IMG
ALIGN="MIDDLE" SRC="./back.gif" BORDER="0"></A><IMG
SRC="./tab.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></TD><TD COLSTART="2"><P ALIGN="CENTER">| <A
HREF="./index.html">Home Page</A> |<BR>| <A HREF="./readme.htm">Read Me</A> | <A
HREF="./news.htm">News &amp; Destinations</A> | |<A HREF="./products.htm">Buy Our Stuff</A> |<BR>| <A
HREF="./study.htm">Study Guide</A> |</P></TD><TD COLSTART="3"><IMG
SRC="./tab.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><A HREF="./readme2.htm"><IMG
ALIGN="MIDDLE" SRC="./forw.gif" BORDER="0"></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
<BR><BR><BR><BR><CENTER><TABLE><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" COLSTART="1">
