<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HTML 
VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD>
<TITLE>Acoma Pueblo - Acoma Sky City Casino</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H1>Acoma Pueblo - Acoma Sky City Casino</H1>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=275>

<P>Acoma Pueblo sits on a high bluff outside Grants, New Mexico. The 
Sky City is one of the oldest continuously inhabited villages in the 
United States. Acoma is justifiably famous for its artists and pottery 
(an Acoma pot was recently given to Sadaam Hussein by New Mexico 
Congressman Bill Richardson), but pottery and tourism is not enough 
to keep the nearly 3,000 tribal members of Acoma economically viable. 
</P>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=325>
<CENTER><a href="./acoma1b.jpg"><IMG src="./acoma1a.gif"></A></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I> Arlene Leon of Acoma Pueblo. Arlene is a single mother 
supporting three girls ages 13, 9, and 6 years old.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR >
<TD WIDTH=325>
<CENTER><a href="./acoma2b.jpg"><IMG src="./acoma2a.gif"></a></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>Michael Weeker of Laguna Pueblo and Shane Garcia of 
Acoma Pueblo. These two young men work at the Sky City Casino. Both 
say this is the best job they can find in the Grants and 
Gallup area.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=275>

<P>The job market in nearby Grants or Gallup is not overwhelmingly 
strong, and many residents have to make the nearly one hour commute 
into Albuquerque every day to keep a good job. The Acoma Sky City 
casino is creating good jobs for members and non-members alike in the 
Grants area. The Sky City casino employs 108 people and allows tribal 
members to take a job with good pay and good benefits close to home.
This is keeping young tribal members at home instead of leaving the 
Pueblo for employment out of the area.  
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<H4>| <a href="./acoma2.htm">More on Acoma Pueblo</a> | <a href="../nmiga/">Return back to Index</a> | </h4>
</CENTER>
</BODY></HTML>
