<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HTML 
VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD>
<TITLE>Acoma Pueblo - raising the standards of living</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H1>Acoma Pueblo - raising the standards of living</H1>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=300>

<P>Acoma is using its gaming revenues to fund programs for the elderly 
and youth programs, but Acoma is also spending a great deal of its 
gaming revenues on upkeep of its outdated and extremely ineffective 
water system. The unique geography of Acoma Pueblo teamed with the 
scarcity of water in the region have caused a great deal of problems 
with the tribe's water system. The wells that pump the water are 
located some 15 miles from Acomita village and Sky City. The water is 
transported those 15 miles by an antiquated pipeline that breaks down 
so often that members never know whether they will get water or
not when they go to the faucet. 
</P>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><a href="./acoma3b.jpg"><IMG src="./acoma3a.gif"></A></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>  Acoma pump house. The water system is so outdated 
Acoma has earmarked $20 million in gaming revenues to build a water 
system that actually works.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR >
<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><a href="./acoma4b.jpg"><IMG src="./acoma4a.gif"></a></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>Old rusted, broken pipes from the Outdated Acoma water 
system.
</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=300>

<P>The old pipes have become inundated with iron oxide, so the water 
sometimes is murky and rusty when it is working. The tribe is 
constantly trying to fix the problem, but the system is so flawed, 
there is no way to fix it little by little. With expected cutbacks 
in the federal budget, Acoma is convinced that the only way to secure 
capital to replace their water system is through constant appeal for 
some federal funding, plus the enhancement of its gaming Operation.  
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
