<TITLE>Santa Ana Pueblo</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H2>Santa Ana Pueblo - renovation and expansion</H2>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD ROWSPAN=3 WIDTH=225>

<P> Santa Ana has recently renovated an abandoned BIA school on its 
property and transformed it into additional office space for tribal 
business management and has office space available for small 
businesses willing to locate on tribal land.</P>

<P>Gaming revenue has also helped the tribe to maintain a championship 
golf course and the Prairie Star restaurant, one of New Mexico's best 
fine dining establishments. In the golf course complex there is also a 
pro shop, a grill for the golfers and a driving range.</P>

<P>Gaming revenues also have provided the money for an expansion and 
renovation of the tribal government offices, and the funding of 
programs for the youth of the tribe and services for the elderly. 
The tribe has recently purchased three new vans to transport the 
elderly to their elderly center and to assist them in shopping and 
other necessary business the elders may have in Albuquerque.
</P>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=375>
<CENTER><a href="./santa4b.jpg"><IMG src="./santa4a.gif" ></a></CENTER>
</center>
<br>
<CENTER><P><I>Abandoned BIA School has been renovated. Now houses 
offices and the Warrior T-shirt Company.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=375>
<CENTER><a href="./santa5b.jpg"><IMG src="./santa5a.gif" ></a></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I> Santa Ana championship golf course. One of the most 
beautiful courses in New Mexico.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=375>
<CENTER><a href="./santa6b.jpg"><IMG src="./santa6a.gif" ></a></CENTER>
<BR>
