<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HTML 
VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD>
<TITLE>Santa Ana Pueblo - additional services through gaming revenue</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H2>Santa Ana Pueblo - additional services through gaming revenue </H2>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD ROWSPAN=3 WIDTH=300>

<P> Santa Ana Pueblo is located approximately 20 miles north of 
Albuquerque and just east of the fastest growing city in the country, 
Rio Rancho. Santa Ana began its gaming operation with Bingo and pull 
tabs in 1993. In this short time, the tribe has used its gaming 
revenues to provide additional services for its members and used its 
gaming revenues to economically diversify the tribe's business 
holdings. Santa Ana provides over 200 jobs for its tribal members and
non-tribal members in its Santa Ana Star casino. The jobs start at a 
very competitive salary and have provided a start in the working world 
for many people in the Pueblo and the surrounding community.</P>

<P>The tribe has expanded its police force, buying several new police 
cars and equipment to deal with crimes committed by non-tribal members 
on tribal land. The tribe is funding scholarships for its bright 
students, and has encouraged the youth of the tribe to strive for a 
better education through its Families and Youth Department and the 
expansion of the community library.</P>

<P>The tribal lands of Santa Ana Pueblo sit along the banks of the Rio 
Grande, and there is an extensive number of ditches that provide water 
for crops in the river valley. Over the years, the ditches had become 
over-grown with weeds and the result was flooding of many homes in low 
lying areas during times of extensive rain-fall. The tribe used gaming 
revenues to buy a bulldozer and pay for its operation in clearing 
miles of overgrown ditches of weeds and other refuse. The result is 
the Pueblo homes are no longer in danger of flooding in the sudden 
rains of New Mexico.
</P>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><a href="./santa1b.jpg"><IMG src="./santa1a.gif" ></a></CENTER>
</center>
<br>
