<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HTML VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD><TITLE>Technology Ventures Corporation - Services / Opportunities for Investment</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>
<body background="./diam2_bg.gif">
<H2>SERVICES</H2>

<P>Technology Ventures is not a funding institution; it is a bridge between technology and investment. Mindful of this role, Technology Ventures offers services to both investors and client companies.</P>

<P>For investors, Technology Ventures screens opportunities carefully, offering only technologies with excellent business potential. Technology Ventures keeps investors informed of such opportunities through various means including the annual New Mexico Equity Capital Symposium. Attended by investors from Wall Street to Main Street, the symposium showcases technology investments of rare quality.</P>

<P>For entrepreneurs, Technology Ventures advises and assists in planning, commercialization strategies and other facets of business organization and start-up, including temporary office space and related services. Technology Ventures also screens investors for client companies.</P>

<P>When appropriate, Technology Ventures assists both parties in the due diligence process.</P>

<center><IMG src="./graph2.jpg"></center>

<H2>OPPORTUNITIES FOR INVESTMENT</H2>

<P></P>

<P>Technology Ventures has only one guiding principle for investment: the right investor for the right technology.</P>

<P>The company looks for core technologies that can be used across a broad spectrum of industries and applications. This approach maximizes the potential impact on the economy and it increases the opportunities for investors who take a technology to market.</P>

<P>There is no set amount of funding required, only that financial resources must be sufficient to bring the technology to fruition. Investments range up to several million dollars, but smaller investments have been made.</P>

<P>The needs of Technology Ventures' clients range from start-up to later-stage funding, but most opportunities are in seed or early-stage phases.</P>

<P>Equity investment is one way that investors can share in the growth. Joint operating partnerships are another. Acquisition arrangements have also been made.</P>

<P></P><center><img src="../images/barpurpl.gif"></center><P></P>
<P>Direct inquires to:</P>

<center><B><ADDRESS>Technology Ventures Corporation</ADDRESS>

<ADDRESS>One Technology Center</ADDRESS>

<ADDRESS>1155 University Boulevard SE</ADDRESS>

<ADDRESS>Albuquerque, New Mexico 87106</ADDRESS>

<ADDRESS>Phone: 505.246.2882</ADDRESS>

<ADDRESS>Fax: 505.246.2891</ADDRESS>

<ADDRESS>E-mail: <a href="mailto:sherman.mccorkle@den.mmc.com">sherman.mccorkle@den.mmc.com</a></ADDRESS></b></center>
