<TITLE>Sandia Pueblo - environmental cleanup and public safety</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H2>Sandia Pueblo - environmental cleanup and public safety</H2></center>
<P>Environmental problems have also been a primary concern for Sandia 
Pueblo. There have been several critical projects completed in a timely
manner that protect and preserve the environment for the residents of 
Sandia Pueblo, and for the surrounding communities. Some of these 
projects include: closing of a former open dump, water monitoring for 
potential contaminants, drinking water testing and analysis, disposal 
of leaking under-ground storage tanks, cleanup of contaminated soil, 
environmental training and education, recycling and community 
awareness. Without gaming dollars, these types of efforts would not 
be possible.</P>

<P>Police protection on the Pueblo has also been provided for by gaming 
revenues. 95% of all calls to the Sandia Police Force concern 
non-tribal members. The police have been provided state-of-the-art 
equipment including cars, a radio system, field drug testing and 
breathalyzer equipment, and protective vests.</P>
<center>
<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=300>
<P><I>(top) Sandia police officer gives a breathalyzer test.</P>

<P>(middle) The Open Dump will be cleaned up and residents will use a 
community waste transfer station</P>

<P>(bottom) New waste transfer station will be operated and maintained 
with gaming revenues.</I></P>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><IMG src="./sand345a.gif"></A></CENTER>
<BR>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
