<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HTML 
VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD>
<TITLE>Isleta - economic diversification program</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H1>Isleta - Economic Diversification Programs</H1>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD ROWSPAN=2 WIDTH=300>

<P>Isleta Pueblo is planning for the future and using the revenues 
from gaming to provide a large number of services to its members 
including programs for the elderly of the community and the youth 
of the community.</P>

<P>The Isleta Gaming Palace is providing jobs for many tribal members 
and non-tribal members from the nearby Albuquerque area. Isleta 
currently employs over 600 people in its gaming, facilities at 
above average pay with a strong benefits package.</P>

<P>The revenues from gaming are providing tribal members with services 
that were currently unavailable because of the lack of tribal funds. 
The Pueblo of Isleta is also planning a strong economic diversification
program and is working to prepare its Pueblo for the future. Isleta 
is located just south of Albuquerque and north of the rapidly growing 
city of Los Lunas. </P>

<P>One of the goals of the economic diversification 
program is to be able to compete with the surrounding communities 
and offer services that will provide even more jobs to the members 
of the Pueblo, and its neighbors. Isleta is aggressively planning 
and reinvesting its gaming revenues in the people of its Pueblo, 
and the surrounding community.</P>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><IMG src="./isl1a.gif" ALT="ISLETA GAMING EMPLOYEES"></CENTER>
</center>
<br>
<CENTER><P><I>Laurie Morton, Marv Garcia, and Sandra Wells. Isleta Gaming Palace 
supplies jobs to over 600 people, both tribal members and citizens of 
the surrounding area.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><IMG src="./isl2a.gif" alt="Isleta governers"></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>Isleta tribal planner Phil Tsosie, Governor Alvino Lucero and Lt. 
Governor Lawrence Lucero.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
