<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HTML 
VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD>
<TITLE>Sandia Pueblo - Casino Sandia</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H1>Sandia Pueblo - Casino Sandia</H1>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=300>

<P>Sandia Pueblo owns and operates Casino Sandia located just north of 
Albuquerque. The Pueblo of Sandia is using its gaming proceeds to 
provide for the needs of its members and is providing jobs at the 
Casino to both tribal members and members of the surrounding 
communities. </P>

<P>Casino Sandia employs 636 people and provides its 
employees with health care and other benefits. The proceeds from 
gaming are being utilized at Sandia to fund extensive programs for 
the children of the tribe as well as to provide for the health and 
safety of all tribal members.</P>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><a href="./sandia1b.jpg"><IMG src="./sandia1a.gif"></A></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>Three workers at Casino Sandia. Casino Sandia now employs 
636 people.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR >
<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><a href="./sandia2b.jpg"><IMG src="./sandia2a.gif"></a></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>Sandia children in the library of the new 
Wellness Center.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=300>

<P>The Wellness Center located near the center of the Pueblo has 
become the gathering place for tribal members of all ages, but 
especially the children of Sandia and the surrounding communities. 
The Wellness Center houses a full-time manager who plans activities 
for the youth of the tribe including basketball and weight training.</P>
 
<P>The Center is also home to a small community library, complete with 
computers For use by tribal members. The library is sup-plied with a 
wealth of information teaching the children of the community the 
importance of their heritage and respect for their culture. The 
Wellness Center also houses a lunch program, Headstart, and youth 
programs.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<H4>| <a href="./sandia2.htm">More on Sandia Pueblo</a> | <a href="../nmiga/">Return back to Index</a> | </h4>
</CENTER>
</BODY></HTML>
