<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HTML 
VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD>
<TITLE>The Pueblo of Pojoaque - Cities of Gold Casino</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H2>The Pueblo of Pojoaque - Cities of Gold Casino</H2>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD ROWSPAN=3 WIDTH=300>

<P>The Pueblo of Pojoaque, located about 15 miles north of Santa Fe, 
is using its gaming operation, The Cities of Gold casino, to finance 
environmental cleanup, infrastructure problems, Indian art and culture,
and economic diversification opportunities for both members of the 
tribe and the surrounding communities.</P>

<P>Since the new Cities of Gold casino opened after the compacts were 
signed by the Governor and approved by the Secretary of the Interior, 
the gaming operation now employs over 700 people, and has expanded 
from 10,000 square feet to approximately 40,000 square feet. </P>

<P>The jobs provided to Pueblo members, and local residents, including 
some of the displaced workers from the Department of Energy downsizing 
at Los Alamos national labs. The gaming operation offers above average 
wages, and a good health and benefit plan for its employees. These 
jobs are especially important in and around the Santa Fe area where 
many local residents are being displaced by rising real estate prices 
and property taxes in Santa Fe. Without a good job, many local 
families would be unable to stay in the area where they were born.
</P>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><a href="./poj1b.jpg"><IMG src="./poj1a.gif" ></a></CENTER>
</center>
<br>
<CENTER><P><I>Entrance to Pojoaque Pueblo Cities of Gold.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><a href="./poj2b.jpg"><IMG src="./poj2a.gif" ></a></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>Tribal and non tribal share a good hand helping maintain good 
customer relations.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><a href="./poj3b.jpg"><IMG src="./poj3a.gif" ></a></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR></TABLE>
<H4>| <a href="./pojoaq2.htm">More on the Pueblo of Pojoaque</a> | <a href="../nmiga/">Return back to Index</a> | </h4>
