VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD>
<TITLE>Isleta - youth program</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H1>Isleta - Youth Programs</H1>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD ROWSPAN=2 WIDTH=300>

<P>Isleta's youth are considered one of the most important reasons for 
its gaming program. All of Isleta's youth programs are funded 100% by 
revenues from gaming. Youth is a constant concern of all Indian people 
and Isleta is no exception. There are over 1200 school age children in 
Isleta, and they are a top priority for the tribe. </P>

<P>The Isleta youth center and recreation area is composed of playing 
fields for baseball, foot-ball and soccer, basketball courts and now 
with the addition to a fully equipped fitness center the youth of 
Isleta have a place to play and be active in a controlled and 
supervised environment. The youth and recreation center also features 
a computer room, television, pool tables, and foosball tables.</P>

<P>The Isleta youth center is constantly supervised and activities are 
planned for youth of all ages. The youth center is open to kids from 
the surrounding community and is one of the most popular hangouts for 
not only the youth of Isleta Pueblo, but also for the youth from Los 
Lunas and Albuquerque, who are interested in having fun in a drug, 
alcohol, and gang-free environment.</P>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><a href="./isl3b.jpg"><IMG src="./isl3a.gif" ALT="ISLETA youth"></a></CENTER>
</center>
<br>
<CENTER><P><I>Youth Program Director Monica Garcia and staff youth 
counselors.  Gaming revenues are providing summer jobs for teens at 
Isleta Pueblo.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><a href="./isl4b.jpg"><IMG src="./isl4a.gif" alt="Isleta youth"></a></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>An Isleta youth lines up his shot at the youth center.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
