<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HTML 
VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD>
<TITLE>San Juan - building for the future</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H1>San Juan - building for the future</H1>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=300>

<P>Without the benefit of gaming revenue, the tribe would not have 
been in the position to secure the capital to begin to develop 
economically in this region. San Juan is also using gaming revenue
to provide necessary services to its members including programs
to care for the tribe's elderly, and scholarship programs for youths
seeking additional education.
</P>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><a href="./sanj4b.jpg"><IMG src="./sanj4a.gif"></A></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>San Juan Pueblos's mini mart stores provide convenient 
quick stops for passing motorists.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR >
<TD WIDTH=300>
<CENTER><a href="./sanj5b.jpg"><IMG src="./sanj5a.gif"></a></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>The Laundromat and car wash provide closer convenience
for tribal members along with their neighboring villages along
Highway 285.
</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=300>

<P>Funds have also been used to expand the Police department as well
as other social service programs benefiting the tribal membership
and the development of infra-structure. In short, the tribal 
government's responsibility has increased due to the availability
of funds brought about through gaming revenues.  The Corporation as well
as the Tribal Government will continue to diversify its economy
through entrepreneurial means.  
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<H4>| <a href="./sanjuan3.htm">More on San Juan</a> | <a href="../nmiga/">Return back to Index</a> | </h4>
</CENTER>
