<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HTML 
VERSION="-//IETF//DTD HTML STRICT LEVEL 2//EN"><HEAD>
<TITLE>Tesuque Pueblo</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H1>Tesuque - restoring traditional beauty</H1>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD ROWSPAN=7 WIDTH=325>

<P>Tesuque Pueblo is using its gaming revenue to restore the 
traditional beauty of its historic plaza. For generations the 
traditional adobe structures surrounding the plaza have been 
slowly deteriorating due to the effects of weather and time on 
the century-old adobes. </P>

<P>Most of the members of the Pueblo had abandoned the sub-standard 
housing on the plaza and had moved into mobile homes or had to rent 
housing away from the Pueblo. The Pueblo of Tesuque used some of its 
gaming revenues to completely renovate the north side of the historic 
plaza. In putting together the renovation plans, Tesuque took great 
steps to preserve the traditional look and feel of their historic plaza</P>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=275>
<CENTER><a href="./tes1b.jpg"><IMG src="./tes1a.gif" ALT="Tesuque Pueblo restoration"></A></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>Tesuque Pueblo Plaza before renovation.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR >
<TD WIDTH=275>
<CENTER><a href="./tes2b.jpg"><IMG src="./tes2a.gif" alt="Tesuque Pueblo Plaze after restoration"></a></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>Tesuque Pueblo Plaza after renovation. The project has 
been funded by gaming dollars and will cost several million dollars to 
complete.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=325>

<P>They followed the plans exactly as the original plaza, which was 
built by their forefathers, with contemporary amenities, including 
rebuilding the infrastructure, including the plumbing and electrical 
system. The renovation project has only just begun, but the results 
are already evident. Many members of the Pueblo that had moved away 
from the plaza are now moving back, and enjoying the contemporary 
housing in a traditional Pueblo setting. </P>

<P>The tribe has completed the north side of the plaza renovation and 
will continue to restore and connect the entire plaza, as it once was 
before.</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<H4>| <a href="./tesuque2.htm">More on Tesuque Pueblo</a> | <a href="../nmiga/">Return back to Index</a> | </h4>

</CENTER>
</BODY></HTML>
