<TITLE>San Juan - Ohkay Casino</TITLE></HEAD><BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER>
<H2>San Juan - Ohkay Casino</H2>

<TABLE WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD ROWSPAN=3 WIDTH=325>

<P>The Pueblo of San Juan, which nests one half mile north of Espanola, 
has a great deal to offer to the city. The TSAY Corporation which is 
the wholly-owned business development entity of the Pueblo operates 
six different enterprises. The corporation employs over 230 people, 
both tribal members as well as Espanola Valley residents. It is 
anticipated that the entire business network will provide over $4 million 
in payroll, and another $2.5 million in goods and services this year. 
With its lands lying within the city limits, there is the opportunity 
for an ideal economic diversification.</P>

<P>The flag ship enterprise is the Ohkay Casino. The gaming revenues 
produced by this tribal enterprise has allowed the Pueblo to incept 
additional profit ventures. The Pueblo recently completed Phase 1 of 
their economic development plan by building a Travel Center which is 
just south of the Ohkay Casino facility. The Travel Center includes 
a convenience store and gas station, complimented by a new Laundromat 
and car wash. Also completed under Phase 1 is the construction of the 
new Ohkay Mini-Mart and RV Park found within the city limits of Espanola 
which includes camp sites, RV Pads, a gas station/convenience store with 
a Laundromat for use by RV campers, and a 100-acre Park containing three 
man-made fishing lakes, along with several nature trails. The development 
of TSAY Construction company has also helped alleviate the need for 
outside construction services on the Pueblo. The construction company
has also ventured outside the reservation boundaries and has begun to 
establish itself as a professional construction development company.
</P>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=275>
<CENTER><a href="./sanj1b.jpg"><IMG src="./sanj1a.gif" ></a></CENTER>
</center>
<br>
<CENTER><P><I>Interior of the Oh-Kay Casino</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=275>
<CENTER><a href="./sanj2b.jpg"><IMG src="./sanj2a.gif" ></a></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>San Juan recreational camp and fishing site.</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=275>
<CENTER><a href="./sanj3b.jpg"><IMG src="./sanj3a.gif" ></a></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><P><I>Mini mart assistant manager Irene Chavez.
</I></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR></TABLE>
