<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Bowhead Transportation Company</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FAEAD8"><TABLE BORDER="0" ALIGN="LEFT"><TR><TD COLSTART="1"><A
HREF="./company.htm"><IMG ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="./images/uicbox.gif" BORDER="0"></A></TD></TR><TR><TD
COLSTART="1"><A HREF="./transportation.htm"><IMG
ALIGN="MIDDLE" SRC="./images/transbox.gif" BORDER="0"></A><IMG
ALIGN="MIDDLE" SRC="./images/point.gif"></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSTART="1"><A
HREF="./lcmf.htm"><IMG ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="./images/lcmfbox.gif" BORDER="0"></A></TD></TR><TR><TD
COLSTART="1"><A HREF="./construction.htm"><IMG
ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="./images/constbox.gif" BORDER="0"></A></TD></TR><TR><TD
COLSTART="1"><A HREF="./umialik.htm"><IMG
ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="./images/umibox.gif" BORDER="0"></A></TD></TR><TR><TD
COLSTART="1"><A HREF="./foundation.htm"><IMG
ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="./images/founbox.gif" BORDER="0"></A></TD></TR><TR><TD
COLSTART="1"><A HREF="./tellus.htm"><IMG
ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="./images/tellbox.gif" BORDER="0"></A></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE><TR><TD
COLSTART="1"></TD><TD COLSTART="2"><IMG ALIGN="TOP" SRC="./images/bowknow.gif"><IMG
ALIGN="RIGHT" SRC="./images/barge.jpg" VSPACE="5" HSPACE="20"><P>Operating exclusively in the Arctic for more than a decade, Bowhead Transportation has now expanded service to include most Western Alaska ports.  Bowhead provides a full complement of marine transportation solutions including Common Carriage, Contract and Charter services.<BR><BR>Direct through cargo service from the Lower 48 to Western Alaska and the North Slope is a mainstay of our business and has been offered each and every summer since 1982.<BR><BR>At Bowhead, remote site service is a specialty.  With the acquisition of the shallow draft tug SADIE and the 180 foot lighterage barge QAYAQ 1, Bowhead is able to provide service to locations unnavigable by deeper draft tow boats and barges.  Cargo loaded to larger line haul barges in Seattle can be lightered off directly to the beach in those areas that are not equipped with docks or terminals.<BR><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" SRC="./images/workmen.jpg" VSPACE="5" HSPACE="20"><BR>The QAYAQ 1 barge is equipped with a 70 ton crane to handle ramps and over-length cargo as well as a full complement of all terrain articulating forklifts capable of handling up to 35,000 pounds.  Our seasoned crew are experts in their field, each with more than 15 years experience in cargo handling in the Arctic and nearly every other village on the coast of Alaska.  We take pride in our ability to complete virtually any job - even under the most adverse conditions.</P><P>A Minority Business Enterprise, Bowhead also operates in and around Washington's Puget Sound.  In addition to our own equipment, our affiliated partners provide access to vessels up to 4000 HP and barges to 330 feet allowing us to complete projects anywhere within the Pacific Rim and Alaska.</P><P><BR>SERVICES AND SOLUTIONS<BR><BR>Call us today to find out how Bowhead can help solve your marine transportation needs, we know the Arctic - and  a whole lot more.<BR><IMG
ALIGN="RIGHT" SRC="./images/loading.jpg" VSPACE="5" HSPACE="20"><BR>Bowhead is a wholly owned subsidiary of Ukpeagvik I&ntilde;upiat Corporation, the native village corporation of Barrow, Alaska.  Named in 1995 as the 10<SUP>th</SUP> largest Alaska-owned corporation by Alaska Business Monthly, UIC and its family of companies provide a wide range of services in Alaska and the Lower 48.  Transportation, Construction, Engineering and Communications are just some of the comprehensive services available.  For more information, contact UIC for a free information package at 907-852-4460 or write to us at PO Box 890, Barrow, AK.  99723.<BR><BR>Bowhead Transportation Co., Inc.<BR>1001 SouthWest Klickitat Way, Suite 104<BR>Seattle, Washington  98134-1161<BR>email: <A
HREF="mailto:info@bowhead.com">info@bowhead.com</A><BR>1-800-347-0049<BR>(206) 763-4524<BR>Fax 206-623-6371</P></TD></TR></TABLE></BODY></HTML>
