<CENTER><BR><H2><A NAME="OTHER">OTHER EVENTS</A></H2></CENTER>
<DL>
<DD><P><B>KTNN Navajo Nights</B>.  A two-hour program every Tuesday evening from 8 p.m. to 10 p.m.  featuring various Native American artists.  Interviews, music, call-in stories, etc. with Host,  Lorie Lee (520) 871-3552.</P></DD><DD><P><B>KTNN DRUMS OF SUMMER</B>.  Held during the months of June, July and August, every  Thursday evenings 8 p.m. to 11 p.m..  Hear the timeless sound of the Drum.  KTNN broadcasts the music of pow wow live from KTNN studios in Window Rock, Arizona or at various locations on the Navajo and Hopi Nations and the surrounding areas.</P></DD><DD><P><B>KAYENTA VISITOR CENTER, KAYENTA, AZ</B>.  Demonstration of crafts daily. Presentations on Navajo culture and dances evenings.  Contact:  Dawn Cody (520) 697-3572.</P></DD></DL><HR
SIZE="4" ALIGN="CENTER"><P><BR><B>TBA: To be announced</B></P>
