<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Navajo Nation - Campgrounds, Rules and regulations, Permit and license fees</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../images/sand.jpg"><CENTER><A HREF="./seal.htm"><IMG
ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="./images/camprule.gif" ALT="Campgrounds, Rules & Regulations, Permit and license fees" BORDER="0"></A></CENTER>
<P><A HREF="./images/assayi2.jpg"><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" SRC="./images/assayi1.jpg" ALT="Assayi Lake"></A></P>
<P><BR><BR></P>
<UL><LI><A HREF="#Navajo"><FONT SIZE="+2">Navajo Nation Park Rules &amp;
Regulations</FONT></A></LI>
<LI><FONT SIZE="+2"><A HREF="#Campgrounds">Campgrounds</A></FONT></LI>
<LI><FONT SIZE="+2"><A HREF="#Permits">Permits, Licenses &amp; Fees</A></FONT></LI></UL>
<P><BR><BR></P>
<HR SIZE="4" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H2><A NAME="Navajo">Navajo</A> Nation Park Rules &amp; Regulations  
</H2>
<OL><LI>Respect the privacy and customs of the Navajo people.  Enter homes
only upon invitation.  Do not wander across residential areas or disturb
property.  Obtain permission before taking pictures of the Navajo people.  A
gratuity may be expected.</LI>
<LI>Please keep Navajoland clean - please do not litter!  Do not burn or bury
trash.  Please place all refuse in trash containers.</LI>
<LI>Fires are permitted only in grills and fireplaces similar control devices. 
No open ground fires in campgrounds.  Please provide your own firewood or
charcoal. 
</LI>
<LI>Please observe quiet hours from 11:00 P.M. to 6:00 am at all camping areas.

</LI>
<LI>Do not disturb or remove animals, plants, rocks, or artifacts as these are
protected by Tribal Antiquity and Federal Laws enforced on the Navajo Nation. 
Rock hunting is prohibited. 
</LI>
<LI>	Rock climbing and off-trail hiking are prohibited.  WARNING!  Loose or
fragile rocks and unfamiliar terrain make climbing and hiking hazardous. 
</LI>
<LI>Possession and consumption of alcoholic beverages are illegal and
prohibited. 
</LI>
<LI>A permit is required for fishing at any lakes, streams, or hunting for game
on land under the jurisdiction of the Navajo Nation.  Permits and information on
fees and dates are available from the Navajo Fish and Wildlife Department
telephone # (520) 871-6451. 
</LI>
<LI>The use of firearms is prohibited on the Navajo Nation. 
</LI>
<LI>The Navajo Nation is not responsible for any injuries, accidents, or thefts
of personal property while traveling through the reservation. 
</LI>
<LI>Please restrict travel to designated trails and established routes.  Off
road travel by four-wheel vehicles, dune buggies, jeeps and motorcycles is
prohibited on back country roads. 
</LI>
<LI>Appropriate dress is requested.  Please no swim wear or bikinis. 
</LI>
<LI>Please maintain pets on a leash or in a confined area.  All		action of pets
are the responsibility of the owner. Campgrounds</LI></OL>
<HR SIZE="4" ALIGN="CENTER">
<CENTER><TABLE WIDTH="575"><TR><TD VALIGN="MIDDLE" COLSTART="1" WIDTH="50%"><H2>Campgrounds</H2></TD>
