<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//SQ//DTD HTML 2.0 HoTMetaL + extensions//EN">
<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>News &amp; Destinations (pt. 2)</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFEBD7" VLINK=#000000><CENTER><IMG ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="./destinr.gif"></CENTER><P><BR></P><TABLE
BORDER="BORDER" CELLPADDING="10" ALIGN="CENTER"><TR><TD
VALIGN="TOP" COLSTART="1" WIDTH="49%"><IMG ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="./newsban.gif"><H3>Five artists win art fellowships</H3>

<P>The Vermont Studio Center announced the winners of the 1995 Educational foundation of America 
Native American Fellowship Awards.  This years awards were expanded from three to five recipients, they are:</P>
<UL><LI>Rose High Bear</LI><LI>Stephen Kiser</LI><LI>Jamison Mahto</LI><LI>Bill Soza</LI><LI>Tex Wounded Face</LI></UL><P>Each EFA Fellow will be awarded a residency from two to eight weeks at the Vermont Studio Center this year.  The residency provides artists with uninterrupted studio time, comfortable housing and meals, plus the companionship of peers and visits from visiting artists and writers.
</P>
<P>Applications for the 1997 NACAP are due October 31, 1996.</P>

<H3>Red Thunder tours with the H.O.R.D.E. Festival</H3><P>Originally scheduled to perform a full-set on the Second Stage for only five tour dates, Red Thunder was invited by Blues Traveler's John Popper to perform a Hoop Dance and prayer song on the main stage following Rusted Root's set. The performance was so popular the band was invited to stay on the whole tour.
Festival-goers can stop by Red Thunder's &quot;Call to Action Tepee&quot; for a drum workshop by singer/songwriter Robby Romero and traditional drummer Benito Concha.</P>

<H3>Hopi Artist Claims best of show at Eiteljorg Indian Market</H3>

<P>A three judge panel named Naavaasya (Hopi) as Best of Show at the Eiteljorg Museum of American Indian and Western Art's fourth annual Indian Market, held June 22-23.  His work, a gold, diamond, and ruby pendant, was cited for its originality and quality.

Thomas Haukaas (Rosebud Sioux) and Stanley Hill (Mohawk) were first and second runners-up respectively.</P>
</TD><TD COLSTART="2" WIDTH="40"></TD><TD
VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="CENTER" COLSTART="3" WIDTH="49%"><IMG
SRC="./iroquois.jpg" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR><FONT Color=#FF00FF <BR>PO Box 7, Caverns Road<BR>Howes Cave, NY 12092<BR>(518) 296-8949</FONT>

<P>Every Wednesday in August  &quot;Family Days,&quot; hands-on activities for all in the Children's Museum, plus lacrosse fun and nature walks.</P>

<P><B>August 2-4</B></P>	
&quot;How Iroquois Traditions Endure&quot;, traditional clay pottery demonstration by artist Roger Perkins, Mohawk from Akwesasne.

<P><B>August 9-11</B></P>	
&quot;How Iroquois Traditions Endure&quot;, trade silver demonstration by silversmith Sheldon Gibson, Onondaga.

<P><B>August 31-September 2</B></P>
&quot;FifteenthAnnual Iroquois Indian Festival&quot;, a three-day event featuring dozens of Iroquois artists and craftspeople, dancers and musicians, storytellers and birds of prey demonstrations, children's activities and native foods.

<P><B>October 3-6</B></P>	
&quot;Sharing the Gifts&quot;, traditional craft demonstration with Peter B.Jones, Onondaga from Cattaraugus, instructing Iroquois apprentices in clay pottery making.

<P><B>Ocober 12-15</B></P>	
&quot;Sharing the Gifts&quot;, craft demonstration with Molly Gabriel, Mohawk from Kahnesatake, instructing Iroquois apprentices in basketmaking.

<P><B>October - December</B></P>	
&quot;Tammy Tarbell Boehning:  Iroquois Art&quot;, an internationally recognized Mohawk potter and sculptor.  Tammy captures the essence of the Native American woman's spiritual way of life and she is the Iroquois Indian Museum's 1996, &quot;Excellence in Iroquois Arts&quot; award.
</TD></TR></TABLE><P><BR></P><CENTER><TABLE><TR><TD COLSTART="1"><A
HREF="./news.htm"><IMG ALIGN="MIDDLE" SRC="./back.gif" BORDER="0"></A><IMG
SRC="./tab.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></TD><TD COLSTART="2"><P ALIGN="CENTER">| <A
HREF="./index.html">Home Page</A> |<BR>| <A HREF="./readme.htm">Read Me</A> | <A
HREF="./news.htm">News &amp; Destinations</A> | |<A HREF="./products.htm">Buy Our Stuff</A> |<BR>| <A
HREF="./study.htm">Study Guide</A> |</P></TD><TD COLSTART="3"><IMG
SRC="./tab.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><A HREF="./news3.htm"><IMG
ALIGN="MIDDLE" SRC="./forw.gif" BORDER="0"></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
