<p>
<br>
<b><font SIZE="6">What's New...</font>
</b>

<P>
<B>Jack Kemp Returns!</B>
<P>
After taking a leave of absence to campaign as Bob Dole's vice-presidential running-mate,  
Empower America co-director Jack Kemp is now back with us.  Stay tuned to this site to see 
what ideas he will be putting on the table in the near future.
<P>
<B>Body Count</B>
<P>
Empower America co-director William J. Bennett has recently released his newest book, Body 
Count, which he co-authored with Professor John DiIulio and John Walters.   The book takes a 
look at the problem of crime in America, especially the prospect of a rising wave in violent 
crimes committed by juveniles.
<P>
<B>Issues</B>
<P>
We are currently improving our web site by creating an archive of various documents produced 
by Empower America.  The archive will be categorized by issue.  Several such issues are already 
up and running.  Click on the issues link in the left margin to see a list of choices.
<P>
<B>New Empower America Study</B>
<P>
On November 7, Empower America held a press conference on Capitol Hill to release a new 
study, In Defense of A Nation, on the contributions of immigrants to the U.S. military.  Look for 
a full text copy of the report to be up on this site soon.  In the meantime, check out what 
Empower America has had to say about immigration in the past.
<P>
<B>Press Conference</B>
<P>
Empower America co-directors Lamar Alexander, William J. Bennett, Jeane Kirkpatrick and Vin 
Weber, and Empower America board member Donald Rumsfeld were all assembled for a press 
conference on November 13th. See excerpts from their remarks on the future of conservatism in 
America.
<P>

