<p>

<a href="/thcc/content/buchanan/buch020697.html"><img src="/thcc/images/buchanan.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="PATRICK J. BUCHANAN">

<b>DON'T MOVE NATO'S RED LINE EAST</b></a><br>The year 1948 was a frightful one. The Red Army had blockaded Berlin.

     Stalinists had taken over Czechoslovakia. The Communist Party was reaching for power in Italy. A ruined

     Germany, split into four occupation zones, was the scene of Nazi war-crimes trials.

<p><br>



<a href="/thcc/content/buchanan/buch020797.html"><img src="/thcc/images/buchanan.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="PATRICK J. BUCHANAN">

<b>STOP FEEDING THE TIGER</b></a><br>February marks the 25th anniversary of the most dramatic summit of the

     Cold War. I can yet recall the motorcade after our 15-person delegation was greeted at the Beijing airport by

     Premier Chou En-lai and his honor guard of handpicked giant soldiers. 

<p><br>



<a href="/thcc/content/greenberg/gree020797.html"><img src="/thcc/images/greenberg.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="Paul Greenberg">

<b>THE ART OF DENIABILITY</b></a><br>You had to identify with Bill Clinton during his first press conference

     the other day -- in much the way visitors gazing at the classic old diorama at

     New York's Museum of Natural History used to identify with the stag

     forever being held at bay by a pack of jackals. 

<p><br>



<a href="/thcc/content/huffington/huff020797.html"><img src="/thcc/images/huffington.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="ARIANNA HUFFINGTON">

<b>A MIND'S JOURNEY THROUGH THE STATE OF THE UNION</b></a><br>In the 19th century, Rossini described Wagner's music as "lovely moments but awful quarters

 of an hour." The same could be said of the president's State of the Union speech this week.

 The best moment came when the president challenged the private sector: "I challenge every

 religious congregation, every community nonprofit, every business to hire someone off

 welfare.

<p><br>



<a href="/thcc/content/sowell/sowe020797.html"><img src="/thcc/images/sowell.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="THOMAS SOWELL">

<b>A WELL-CONCEIVED FRAUD</b></a><br>If you think "ebonics" or "black English" is an ill-conceived attempt to

     educate black children in Oakland, then you are very mistaken. It is a well-conceived way for the Oakland

     school board to evade responsibility for bad academic results and to get federal money.

<p><br>



<a href="/thcc/content/sowell/sowe020897.html"><img src="/thcc/images/sowell.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Thomas Sowell">

<b>CRUELTY TO THE INNOCENT</b></a><br>One of the signs of our times is a San Francisco Chronicle news story about

     a man "who confessed to terrorizing more than 100 women in California" and was scheduled to be released on

     February 5th from a "corrections camp" where he has been "a resident, not an inmate" while he was "serving out

     his parole," despite protests from law enforcement officials and local citizens.

<p><br>



<a href="/thcc/content/tyrrell/tyrr020797.html"><img src="/thcc/images/tyrrell.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="R. EMMETT TYRRELL JR.">

<b>PUBLIC NUISANCES</b></a><br>The other night, while the Boy President was practicing his smirks before the

 mirror prefatory to delivering his State of the Union balderdash, Paul Weyrich, the

 legendary conservative activist, was conducting an interview on his television show on NET,

 a conservative channel network that he runs.

<p><br>










</blockquote>



















